---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Formula 1 Inspired Incense Burner">

    <main class="main">

    <!-- Page Title -->
    <div class="page-title">
      <div class="breadcrumbs">
        <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
          <ol class="breadcrumb">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/"><i class="bi bi-house"></i> Home</a></li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/portfolio">Portfolio</a></li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active current">Formula 1 Inspired Incense Burner</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <div class="container section-title pb-0">
        <h2>Formula 1 Inspired Incense Burner</h2>
        <div class="title-shape">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 200 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M 0,10 C 40,0 60,20 100,10 C 140,0 160,20 200,10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div><!-- End Section Title -->
    </div><!-- End Page Title -->

    <!-- Portfolio Details Section -->
    <section id="portfolio-details" class="portfolio-details section">

      <div class="container">

        <div class="row gy-4 g-lg-5">
          <div class="col-lg-6">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/1.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/2.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/3.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/4.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
            <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/5.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4 rounded-4" alt="" loading="lazy">
          </div>

          <div class="col-lg-6">

            <div class="position-sticky" style="top: 40px">
              <div class="portfolio-description">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>
                  Formula 1 inspired incense burner developed from a client concept, integrating automotive styling with functional airflow design for consumer product manufacturing.
                </p>

                <div class="portfolio-info mt-5">
                  <h2>Specifications</h2>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Type:</strong> Consumer product concept</li>
                    <li><strong>Inspiration:</strong> Formula 1 vehicle geometry</li>
                    <li><strong>Manufacturing:</strong> Injection molding</li>
                    <li><strong>Function:</strong> Rear exhaust-based smoke output</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <h2>Design Constraints</h2>
                <p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Maintain compact dimensions defined by client</li>
                    <li>Integrate incense chamber within rear section</li>
                    <li>Ensure airflow exits through exhaust pipe</li>
                    <li>Adapt complex geometry for manufacturable form</li>
                  </ul>
                </p>

                <div class="testimonial-item">
                  <p>
                    <h2>⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐</h2>
                  </p>
                  <div>
                    <h3>Yassin Lalmi</h3>
                    <h4>Client</h4>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Design Approach</h2>
                <p>
                  The base geometry was derived from a Formula 1 vehicle model, with modifications applied to accommodate an internal incense chamber and airflow pathway.
                  <br><br>
                  The rear section was redesigned to guide smoke through the exhaust outlet, ensuring a clear and controlled visual effect while maintaining overall form consistency.
                </p>

                <h2>Key Features</h2>
                <p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Functional incense chamber integrated within vehicle body</li>
                    <li>Customized exhaust system for directed smoke flow</li>
                    <li>Highly detailed external geometry based on F1 design</li>
                    <li>Geometry adapted for injection molding feasibility</li>
                  </ul>
                </p>

                <h2>Deliverables</h2>
                <p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Complete 3D CAD model ready for manufacturing</li>
                    <li>Modified geometry for internal incense placement</li>
                    <li>Design suitable for injection molding production</li>
                    <li>High-detail visual model for product presentation</li>
                  </ul>
                </p>

                <h2>Outcome</h2>
                <p>
                  Delivered a manufacturable product concept combining aesthetic fidelity with functional airflow design, enabling real-world production of a unique consumer item.
                </p>

              </div>

              <div class="portfolio-info mt-5">
                <h3>Project information</h3>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Category</strong> Client Project</li>
                  <li><strong>Client</strong> Yassin Lalmi</li>
                  <li><strong>Project date</strong> December, 2025</li>
                  <li><a href="https://www.upwork.com/freelancers/numanzamandipuu" class="btn-visit align-self-start" target="_blank">View Project on Upwork</a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </section><!-- /Portfolio Details Section -->

    </main>

</BaseLayout>